# Switch

A binary toggle for settings that take effect immediately.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.horizontal(), attribute.class("w-fit")], [
    switch.input([
      attribute.id("intro-notifications"),
      attribute.checked(True),
    ]),
    field.label([attribute.for("intro-notifications")], [
      html.text("Enable notifications"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add switch
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  switch.input([])
}
```

## Examples

Size the switch with an attribute, pair it with field helpers, or set its state with standard attributes.

### Sizes

Pass the small size attribute to fit dense toolbars and inline controls.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.horizontal(), attribute.class("w-fit")], [
    field.root([field.horizontal()], [
      switch.input([switch.sm(), attribute.id("size-small")]),
      field.label([attribute.for("size-small")], [html.text("Small")]),
    ]),
    field.root([field.horizontal()], [
      switch.input([attribute.id("size-medium")]),
      field.label([attribute.for("size-medium")], [html.text("Medium")]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Label

Pair the switch with a horizontal field and label to extend the click target and announce the option.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.horizontal(), attribute.class("w-fit")], [
    switch.input([attribute.id("marketing-emails"), attribute.checked(True)]),
    field.label([attribute.for("marketing-emails")], [
      html.text("Send me marketing emails"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Invalid

Set aria-invalid with a field error to surface validation errors.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-fit")], [
    field.root([field.horizontal()], [
      switch.input([
        attribute.id("accept-policy"),
        attribute.aria_invalid("true"),
      ]),
      field.label([attribute.for("accept-policy")], [
        html.text("Accept the privacy policy"),
      ]),
    ]),
    field.error([], [html.text("You must accept to continue.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Disabled

Pass the disabled attribute to prevent interaction and remove the switch from the focus order.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-fit")], [
    field.root([field.horizontal()], [
      switch.input([
        attribute.id("disabled-analytics"),
        attribute.disabled(True),
      ]),
      field.label([attribute.for("disabled-analytics")], [
        html.text("Share usage analytics"),
      ]),
    ]),
    field.root([field.horizontal()], [
      switch.input([
        attribute.id("disabled-updates"),
        attribute.disabled(True),
        attribute.checked(True),
      ]),
      field.label([attribute.for("disabled-updates")], [
        html.text("Install updates automatically"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Elements

A single element wrapping a native input so the thumb can layer on top.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `switch.input(attrs)` | Renders the track, the native input, and the sliding thumb. |

### Size Attributes

Adjusts the track and thumb dimensions.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `switch.sm()` | Small, for dense toolbars, table rows, and inline controls. |
| `switch.md()` | Medium, the default; matches a switch with no size attribute. |

### Attributes

Standard Lustre attributes the switch responds to. Pass them through the input's attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `attribute.checked(True)` | Fills the track with the primary surface and slides the thumb to the on edge. |
| `attribute.disabled(True)` | Locks the switch, dims it, and removes it from the focus order. |
| `attribute.required(True)` | Marks the switch as required and reveals the field label's indicator. |
| `attribute.aria_invalid("true")` | Surfaces the destructive border and ring on validation failure. |
| `attribute.name("notifications")` | Form field name submitted with the parent form. |
| `attribute.value("enabled")` | Submitted value when checked. Defaults to "on". |
| `attribute.id("notifications")` | Pair with field.label's for attribute to extend the click target. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the switch's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="switch"]` | The root container wrapping the input and thumb. |
| `[data-slot="switch"]:has(> input[data-size="sm\|md"])` | The root, tagged with its active size. |
| `[data-slot="switch"] > input` | The native input control. |
| `[data-slot="switch"]:has(> input:checked)` | The root, when its input is checked. |
| `[data-slot="switch"]:has(> input:disabled)` | The root, when locked. |
| `[data-slot="switch"]:has(> input[aria-invalid="true"])` | The root, flagged with a validation failure. |
| `[data-slot="switch-thumb"]` | The thumb that slides across the track. |

## Accessibility

**Native semantics, keyboard ready.** Renders a native `<input type="checkbox">` with role="switch", so the browser handles toggling, focus, and form submission while assistive tech announces it as an on/off switch. Pair every switch with a field label so screen readers announce what the toggle controls.

### Keyboard

| Key | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Tab | Move focus to the switch. |
| Shift + Tab | Move focus to the previous focusable element. |
| Space | Toggle the on/off state. |

